      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "### Cluster Creation\n\nHealth view for HCP cluster creation from backend cluster-create operation metrics.\n\n**How the time range works**\n- The dashboard time picker is the lookback window (default `last 24 hours`).\n- `Completed`, `Successful`, `Failed / Canceled`, `Success SLO`, `Timeliness SLO`, and `Create Duration p50/p95/p99` count cluster `operation_type=create` attempts that reached a terminal phase within the selected window.\n- `Successful` means `phase=\"succeeded\"`; `Failed / Canceled` means `phase=~\"failed|canceled\"`.\n- Use `24h` by default; `7d` is the practical upper bound for the current retained operation history.\n\n**Datasource**\n- Select a single service-cluster Prometheus datasource from the top bar.\n- Metrics come from backend service clusters (`Managed_Prometheus_services-*`).\n\n**Primary signals**\n- `Success SLO` = succeeded share among terminal create attempts in the selected window.\n- `Timeliness SLO` = share of successful create attempts that completed within 20 minutes.\n- `Create Duration p50/p95/p99` = create-duration percentiles for successful attempts.\n- `Create Ops Stuck > 20 min` should stay at 0.\n\n**Provisioning states**\n- accepted, provisioning, updating, deleting, succeeded, failed, canceled, awaitingsecret",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.6.9",
      "title": "Dashboard Info",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "datasource",
        "uid": "-- Mixed --"
